owl:Ontology.dc:creator: Ed Shaya
owl:Ontology.dc:description: This ontology covers classes and properties in chemistry that are commonly used by astronomers. It includes terms from the IVOA Thesaurus plus terms from the UMD astronomical ontology
owl:Ontology.dc:title: chemistry.owl

owl:Class.skos:definition: a chemical substance that is composed of a particular set of molecules or ions. Two or more elements combined into one substance, through a chemical reaction, form what is called a chemical compound

owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical element
owl:Class.skos:definition: a chemical substance that is made up of a particular kind of atoms and hence cannot be broken down or transformed by a chemical reaction into a different element, though it can be transmutated into another element through a nuclear reaction

owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical Substance
owl:Class.skos:definition: any material with a definite chemical composition

owl:Class.rdfs:label: P-branch
owl:Class.skos:definition: A set of lines in the spectra of molecules corresponding to unit increases in rotational energy.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Q-branch
owl:Class.skos:definition: A set of lines in the spectra of molecules corresponding to unit increases in vibrational energy.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: radical
owl:Class.skos:definition: atomic or molecular species with unpaired electrons on an otherwise open shell configuration. These unpaired electrons are usually highly reactive

owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: The term chiral is used to describe an object that is non-superimposable on its mirror image. Usually chirality of isomers are designated left-handed or right-handed. Other designations are R/S (for configurations), +/- and d/l (for optical activity). or D/L
